# Architecture Rules

## Project Type
Multi-tenant cloud workspace + AI agent platform.

## Service Boundaries
- auth-service: identity, sessions, OAuth
- workspace-service: file storage, quotas
- runtime-service: code execution sandboxes
- agent-service: AI orchestration, tool calling
- memory-service: long-term memory, embeddings
- publish-service: app deployment

## Cross-Service Communication
- Internal: HTTP with service auth tokens
- Async: Redis pub/sub or BullMQ
- No direct DB access across services

## Tenant Isolation
- Every query MUST scope by user_id or organization_id
- No raw SQL without tenant filter
- Storage paths prefixed with tenant ID

## State Management
- PostgreSQL: source of truth
- Redis: cache, sessions, rate limits, queues
- MinIO/S3: file content, build artifacts

## Code Organization
- Each service in `services/<name>/`
- Shared types in `packages/shared/`
- DB schema in `packages/db/`
- Each service exports: routes, services, repositories, types

## Module Pattern
- Repository: pure DB access
- Service: business logic
- Controller/Route: HTTP handler + validation
- DTOs: Zod schemas in shared

## Error Handling
- Custom error classes (AppError, AuthError, ValidationError, etc.)
- Never leak internal errors to client
- Always log with correlation ID
- HTTP status codes consistent

## Logging
- Structured JSON via pino
- Required fields: timestamp, level, correlationId, userId, service
- No PII in logs (mask emails, redact tokens)

## Configuration
- Environment variables only
- Validated at startup with Zod
- No hardcoded secrets
- Different configs per environment

## Dependencies
- Prefer standard library
- Add deps only when justified
- Pin versions
- Audit regularly